===== Setting the rules for evolutionary tree of thought =====
Below is an illustration of a collaborative multiâ€expert process. In our imagined roundâ€table, three experts independently proposed a oneâ€step idea, then exchanged notes. They distilled a set of key inspirations (for example, â€œnanostructuring to decouple electron/phonon transportâ€, â€œdefect/doping engineering of established thermoelectric compoundsâ€, and â€œhybrid organicâ€“inorganic routes introducing novel carrierâ€modulation mechanismsâ€). After â€œmutationâ€ (adjusting parameters) and â€œcrossoverâ€ (blending ideas) and then verifying that the proposals obey basic physical laws and are at least somewhat computationally and synthetically accessible, the experts converged on three candidate hypotheses. Each hypothesis was then run through a twoâ€stage assessment: first, a decisionâ€tree check for physical/chemical consistency and feasibility, and then a scoring framework using five criteria. The following is a summary of the three final hypotheses along with their decisionâ€tree checkpoints and evaluation scores.

