Develop a thermoelectric material based on a 2D layered semiconductor (for example, transition metal dichalcogenides) in which colloidal quantum dots are self-assembled between the layers. The quantum dots serve to scatter midâ€frequency phonons (thus reducing thermal conductivity) while preserving high carrier mobility. This â€œphononâ€glass electronâ€crystalâ€ approach is enhanced by controllable dot size and interâ€layer spacing.

